  "title" : "How to download content from URL using Jsoup and Java",
  "body" : "<p>I have this code which extracts all links from an URL using JSOUP. I need to put all the content from these links into a txt. How can I do this using Java?</p>\n<pre><code>public class Main {\n  public static void main(String[] args) {\n    Document doc, content;\n    try {\n        doc = Jsoup.connect(&quot;http://fmi.unibuc.ro/ro&quot;).get();\n        System.out.print(doc);\n\n        Elements links = doc.select(&quot;a[href]&quot;);\n        for (Element link : links) {\n\n            System.out.println(&quot;\\nlink : &quot; + link.attr(&quot;href&quot;));\n        }\n    } catch (IOException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    }\n  }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
